Before reinstall:
- Install iso, burn with etcher or dd
- Check the checksum of the iso https://wiki.manjaro.org/index.php?title=Burn_an_ISO_File

To automate the following:
- sudo pacman -Syuu
- Install yaourt (put this after symlinks, bc need the -y flag)
- Yaourt google-chrome and then login to google
- Sync google bookmarks + extensions (takes a while)
- Sync up start menu (using menulibre?)
- Disable screensavers
- Change power management settings

Software:
- Download and setup papirus icons https://github.com/PapirusDevelopmentTeam/papirus-icon-theme
- set resolution (1600x900)?
- Minimise taskbar to bottom right
- install network-manager or wicd
- install ksysguard (task manager) && htop
- install seahorse (gui for gnome-keyring)  https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/GNOME/Keyring (saves skype login)
- Install nano, kate, and vscode (text editors) (and then run extension install from above)

- Install konsole, or xfce4-terminal
- install zsh, and oh-my-zsh https://github.com/ohmyzsh/ohmyzsh + theme https://github.com/jopcode/oh-my-zsh-bunnyruni-theme
- xkill
- yaourt fluxgui, and set temp to min, latitude: -33.7502
- gimp, mypaint, gwenview/ristretto
- variety-git and download google earth view, and set
- gnome-screenshot, keybind to printscreen
- keybind terminal opening to f12 (xfce4-terminal/konsole)
- vlc, cheese, transmission, kazam, obs project, zoom, slack
- ffmpeg, banshee?, 
- skype-for-linux or yaourt -S skypeforlinux-stable-bin
- steam
- https://create.arduino.cc/getting-started/plugin ?

- For slack, remove default start script and place the following with sudo chmod +x to it in /usr/local/bin and add back to autostart scripts: #!/bin/bash env LD_PRELOAD=/usr/lib/libcurl.so.3 /usr/bin/slack %U -u &
- okular, libreoffice, anki, thunar (and set default)
- gparted, etcher

